The paper discusses the design and evaluation of a numeric static analysis for Java, which falls under the programming languages (cs.PL) and software engineering (cs.SE) sub-categories. The evaluation focuses on the precision and performance of the analysis, which could also be relevant to the cryptography and security (cs.CR), logic in computer science (cs.LO), and systems and control (cs.SY) sub-categories.
